<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Flint, Mich. Fears Serial Killer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FLINT, Mich. (AP) -- At least four women with a history of drug  
use or prostitution have been slain in Flint over the past eight 
months in what investigators say may be the work of a serial 
killer. 
</P>
<P>
	The police and the FBI have formed a task force to investigate.  
It met for the first time Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The bodies of all four women were found in or near abandoned  
houses. All were black women in their late 20s or 30s. Police would 
not say how the women died, but The Flint Journal said one had been 
strangled. 
</P>
<P>
	The police vice squad was put on alert to watch for people who  
try to solicit prostitutes. 
</P>
<P>
	The most recent victim was found Friday by a passerby. The first  
victim was discovered in an abandoned house in February. 
</P>
<P>
	The FBI behavioral sciences unit will try to construct a  
psychological profile of the killer. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
