<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-11 20:50:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boston's Martinez Saves Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Pedro Martinez took on an unfamiliar role to  
rescue the Boston Red Sox from an all-too-familiar situation. 
</P>
<P>
	The injured ace came in from the bullpen to save Boston from  
elimination on Monday night, striking out eight in six hitless 
innings as the Red Sox beat Cleveland 12-8 to earn a chance to play 
the New York Yankees for the American League pennant. 
</P>
<P>
	With Game 5 of their first-round AL playoff series against  
Cleveland tied 8-8 and looking a lot like the previous night's 
slugfest, Martinez started the fourth inning and shut the Indians 
down from there. 
</P>
<P>
	He threw Sandy Alomar a 91 mph fastball for his first pitch and  
retired Cleveland in order in the fourth -- the first 1-2-3 inning 
of the game for the Indians batters. He fanned two in the fifth, 
sixth and seventh innings; Jim Thome, who homered twice before 
Martinez entered the game, struck out looking to start the eighth 
to become Martinez' seventh victim. 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez strained a muscle in his right shoulder in Game 1, an  
injury that seemed to doom Boston's chances of surviving the first 
round of the AL playoffs. But after two consecutive Red Sox 
victories, including Sunday night's 23-7 beating, the teams 
returned to Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
	That gave Martinez another day to recover -- just enough time, it  
turns out. 
</P>
<P>
	He wasn't cleared to pitch until he had thrown a dozen warmup  
pitches before the game. By the third, though, he removed any doubt 
that he would be available. 
</P>
<P>
	``Ouch!'' pitching coach Joe Kerrigan said as the ball popped  
into his catcher's mitt. 
</P>
<P>
	After just one minute of catch in right field, the Red Sox ace  
was declared ready for action. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's had a steady progression of feeling better the last three  
days. So that's a good sign,'' Boston manager Jimy Williams said 
before the game. ``I really think he can pitch.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez was the best pitcher in baseball this season, leading  
the major leagues with a 23-4 record and 2.07 ERA while striking 
out a career-high 313 batters. But he left Game 1 after four 
innings because of a strained muscle under his right shoulder 
blade. 
</P>
<P>
	The Red Sox lost the first two games of the series, extending  
their postseason futility streak to 18 losses in 19 games. So when 
Martinez could barely pick up a ball before Game 3, it didn't seem 
to matter. 
</P>
<P>
	But with Boston winning Saturday and Sunday, Martinez's  
condition became an issue again. And though Bret Saberhagen started 
Monday night, the prospect of Martinez coming out of the bullpen 
energized his team. 
</P>
<P>
	``If he's near 100 percent, obviously it would be a tremendous  
boost,'' reliever Derek Lowe said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
