<HEADLINE> BBC Can't Air George Michael Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- George Michael refused to let the British  
Broadcasting Corp. air footage from his NetAid performance after 
technical glitches marred his show. 
</P>
<P>
	Michael was among dozens of performers to appear at three  
overlapping fundraising concerts Saturday in London, Geneva and New 
Jersey. The events were organized by the United Nations Development 
Program and broadcast live on the Internet, where viewers were 
encouraged to donate money to help the world's impoverished. 
</P>
<P>
	Michael's show at London's Wembley Stadium was blighted by  
technical problems that led him to prohibit the BBC from showing 
any part of his performance when the network screened concert 
segments, said Andy Stephens, Michael's manager. 
</P>
<P>
	``We would love to have shown it to his fans, as we are  
completely satisfied with it, and we are disappointed that we were 
not allowed to use it,'' a BBC spokesman said, speaking with 
customary anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
	Stephens said the technical glitches may be able to be patched  
up for future broadcasts. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
