<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hickman wins Tufts 10K Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Libby Hickman defended her title Monday, breaking  
away from South Africa's Colleen DeReuck in the final 300 meters to 
win the Tufts Health Plan 10K. 
</P>
<P>
	Hickman, DeReuck and Kenya's Jane Ngotho ran in a tight trio  
until Hickman picked up the pace in the race's final kilometer. 
Ngotho dropped off first, then DeRueck fell behind as the runners 
turned the corner toward the Charles Street finish line. 
</P>
<P>
	The 34-year-old Hickman, of Fort Collins, Colo., finished in  
32:48, comfortably ahead of DeReuck, who came in at 32:54. Ngotho 
finished at 33:00. 
</P>
<P>
	Jane Omoro of Kenya (33:07) and Lieve Slegers of Belgium (33:36)  
rounded out the top 5. 
</P>
<P>
	The all-women's race, sanctioned by USA Track &AMP; Field, decides  
the national women's 10K champion. 
</P>
<P>
	The 23rd annual race featured nearly 7,000 runners.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
