<HEADLINE> Lucent Plans Mobile Phones in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEIJING (AP) -- China's Konka Group and Lucent Technologies Inc.  
have agreed to develop an advanced mobile phone for the Chinese 
market, the state-run Xinhua News Agency reported. 
</P>
<P>
	They plan to develop a phone ``characterized by high speed data  
transmission, advanced language and image processing technology, 
and very low energy consumption,'' Xinhua said in a report late 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Konka is confident of having 20 percent of the domestic mobile  
phone market in three years,'' Konka Group general manager Chen 
Weirong told Xinhua. 
</P>
<P>
	Konka is one of China's largest makers of home appliances,  
specializing in color televisions for export, and lists B-shares 
for foreign investors on the Shenzhen stock exchange. The 
technology cooperation deal with Lucent, based in Murray Hill, 
N.J., will allow Konka to diversify into the telecommunications 
field. 
</P>
<P>
	China's mobile phone market is growing quickly. Information  
Industry Minister Wu Jichuan told a forum in Geneva that he expects 
mobile phone subscribers to increase from 26 million to about 200 
million within the next decade, Xinhua said. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
