<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-11 18:20:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> TCU Added to Conference USA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Conference USA presidents unanimously approved the addition of  
TCU to the league in all sports on Monday, but passed on another 
WAC team from the Dallas-Fort Worth market. 
</P>
<P>
	TCU, a former Southwest Conference member now in the Western  
Athletic Conference, will join C-USA in all sports in 2001, two 
years before current league member South Florida will begin 
competing for the football title, the presidents of the current 
C-USA schools decided. 
</P>
<P>
	With the additions, Conference USA will have 11 football  
schools. Currently, the 4-year-old football league sports two Top 
25 teams for the first time, No. 23 East Carolina and No. 25 
Southern Mississippi. 
</P>
<P>
	C-USA presidents, however, didn't vote to extend an invitation  
to SMU and commissioner Mike Slive said that decision was based on 
numbers. 
</P>
<P>
	``Clearly, as we got down to the end of the day, it's a great  
program, but size was an issue. The board decided to take care of 
current members,'' Slive said of SMU during a teleconference from 
New York, where the presidents met. 
</P>
<P>
	Slive refused to discuss the actual voting, but said the  
league's board of directors has finished its work on expansion for 
now. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to TCU's addition to the league in all sports, the  
presidents acted on two proposals concerning current C-USA members. 
</P>
<P>
	The first was South Florida, a C-USA member in all sports but  
football, will begin conference football play in 2003, two years 
after it first begins play on the NCAA Division I-A level. The 
other has East Carolina, now a football-only member, joining the 
league in all other sports in 2001. 
</P>
<P>
	TCU looked at the move as a step toward more national exposure.  
</P>
<P>
	``Most of our out-of-state students come from the Midwestern  
corridor of the country, and as a member of C-USA, TCU will gain 
exposure to an extremely high percentage of the nation's 
population, the media centers and large urban areas of the Central 
and Eastern time zones,'' athletic director Eric Hyman said. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to 11 football-playing teams, C-USA will expand its  
men's and women's basketball leagues to 14 teams each. 
</P>
<P>
	The 11 football members will leave C-USA one team short of being  
able to stage a league championship team. 
</P>
<P>
	``The issue of how many football schools was certainly a topic  
of conversation, but the board was comfortable at this point of 
staying at 11, and not going to 12,'' Slive said. ``That's not a 
driving force in our thinking.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The league's football teams -- Army, UAB, Cincinnati, East  
Carolina, Houston, Louisville, Memphis, Southern Miss and Tulane -- 
are playing six league games this year, and that number was already 
scheduled to increase to seven in 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	Slive is not sure how the addition of two teams will affect  
future football scheduling, but indicated the league was not ready 
to switch to divisions in football. 
</P>
<P>
	In basketball, the league has two six-team divisions. Each  
division will likely increase by one. 
</P>
<P>
	While East Carolina and Army are currently football-only members  
of C-USA, DePaul, Marquette, NC-Charlotte, Saint Louis and South 
Florida are league members in basketball and other sports except 
football. 
</P>
<P>
	TCU's departure leaves the WAC, which was a 16-school league the  
last two years until eight members defected to form the Mountain 
West Conference, with eight schools as Nevada joins next season. 
</P>
<P>
	``We don't feel that the loss of one university, no matter who  
it is, is a death blow by any means,'' senior associate 
commissioner Jeff Hurd said. ``We still consider ourselves a viable 
division one conference and we'll explore what options we have.'' 
</P>
<P>
	With Nevada joining the conference next season, TCU's exit would  
leave the conference with eight teams. 
</P>
<P>
	``We might stay at eight teams,'' Hurd said. ``There are several  
eight team conferences around the country, it could be that eight 
is the number or we'll go beyond that,'' and try to get other teams 
to join the conference. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
