<HEADLINE> Anaheim Angels Get Two Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Reliever Pep Harris and infielder Justin  
Baughman, both sidelined for the 1999 season after undergoing 
surgery, were designated for assignment Monday by the Anaheim 
Angels. 
</P>
<P>
	Harris, 27, underwent reconstructive surgery on his right elbow  
last December. 
</P>
<P>
	Baughman, 25, was recovering from surgery to repair multiple  
fractures of his lower left leg, an injury sustained Nov. 7, 1998, 
while he was playing with Los Mochis of the Mexican League. 
</P>
<P>
	The Angels also assigned pitcher Steve Mintz to Triple-A  
Edmonton. 
  	   	
