<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Police: Man Threw Wife Over Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- A man has been charged with murdering  
his wife by throwing her off the towering Dames Point Bridge after 
a fight. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas H. Groover, 38, was arrested Sunday after the body of  
Teresa Groover, 32, was found floating near Blount Island, near 
downtown Jacksonville. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said the two began arguing at a lounge. On the way home,  
he stopped the car on the bridge and they continued the argument. 
</P>
<P>
	At first, he pushed her over the rail of the bridge and she  
landed on an apron used by maintenance workers, police said. He 
then pushed her off the ledge, 160 feet into the St. Johns River, 
said Sgt. Andy Joiner. 
</P>
<P>
	Groover reported his wife missing but was brought in for  
questioning when her body was found. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said Groover admitted throwing his wife off the bridge.  
</P>
<P>
	Groover, charged with murder, was being held without bond in the  
county jail. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
