<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Makes IMF Loan Payment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- The Russian government made an $83 million payment  
to the International Monetary Fund, the Finance Ministry said in a 
statement Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Russia is the IMF's biggest debtor, with more than $15 billion  
in outstanding loans. 
</P>
<P>
	The country's latest loan with the IMF, an 18-month $4.5 billion  
arrangement, has been delayed following allegations of money 
laundering in Russia. 
</P>
<P>
	Russian officials have said payments due to the IMF through the  
end of the year would be unaffected by any delay in loan 
disbursements. The latest payment was made Friday, the ministry 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	A second installment of $640 million on the current loan was  
expected in September but is unlikely to be delivered to Russia 
before November at the earliest, officials have said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
