<HEADLINE> Ambassador Crotty Dead at 68 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GAINESVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- E. William Crotty, a major Democratic  
fund-raiser who became U.S. Ambassador to the Eastern Caribbean 
last year, has died of pneumonia. He was 68. 
</P>
<P>
	Crotty died Sunday at a Gainesville hospital.  
</P>
<P>
	Crotty, a longtime Daytona Beach attorney and civic activist,  
was ambassador to seven nations -- Barbados, Antigua and Barbuda, 
Dominica, St. Lucia, Grenada, St. Kitts and Nevis, and St. Vincent 
and The Grenadines. He was appointed to the post in November and 
was based in Barbados. 
</P>
<P>
	He was former chairman of the Executive Committee of the  
Democratic National Committee Board of Directors and a fervent 
fund-raiser for numerous candidates, including President Clinton 
and Vice President Al Gore. 
</P>
<P>
	``William Crotty was a terrific statesman, a committed Democrat  
and a friend who will be missed,'' Gore said in a statement. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
