<HEADLINE> Billy Davis Jr. Marks Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- As they celebrated their 30th year of  
marriage, Grammy-winning couple Billy Davis Jr. and Marilyn McCoo 
were quietly agonizing. 
</P>
<P>
	Last June, the 61-year-old Davis learned he had prostate cancer.  
</P>
<P>
	``That was the hardest part, just hearing those dreaded words:  
You have cancer,'' Davis said Monday. ``Your immediate reaction is, 
'This is a death sentence.' But it's not, and I think it's 
important that other men realize that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	His prostate was removed in August, shortly after the couple  
celebrated their anniversary. Davis said the cancer had not spread 
beyond the prostate, and he opted for surgery over radiation. 
</P>
<P>
	When he awoke in the recovery room, Davis was concerned about  
one thing -- his wife. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was worried that no one had told her I was fine, and I asked  
for her. After 30 years, it was like asking for my right arm,'' he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The couple met as members of the multiple Grammy-winning group  
The Fifth Dimension in 1965. They left the band to record together, 
winning a Grammy in 1976 for ``You Don't Have to be a Star (To Be 
in My Show).'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
