<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Britain's GEC To Become Marconi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The General Electric Company PLC, Britain's  
biggest electrical engineering company, said Monday that it will 
change its name to Marconi PLC. 
</P>
<P>
	The change will become effective once GEC completes the sale of  
its Marconi Electronics Systems business to British Aerospace PLC. 
</P>
<P>
	The name change symbolizes GEC's transformation from an  
industrial and defense electronics group into an information 
technology company. 
</P>
<P>
	The Marconi brand, long a part of GEC's business, is named for  
Italian physicist Guglielmo Marconi, who pioneered wireless 
telegraphy. Marconi PLC will be split into three businesses -- 
communications, systems and capital. 
</P>
<P>
	GEC said it plans to list shares in the renamed company in the  
United States some time next year. It said it expects that Marconi 
PLC will be listed on the London Stock Exchange and will be a part 
of the FTSE-100 index. 
</P>
<P>
	Marconi Electronics Systems comprises operations in aerospace,  
naval shipbuilding and defense electronics. GEC agreed in April to 
sell the business to British Aerospace. The $11.6 billion deal 
would be the largest defense-industry combination in Europe. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
