<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Mixed; Gold Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed against most other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold prices fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0636 in late European trading, down  
from $1.0671 Friday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the euro 
traded at $1.0634. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Friday,  
included 106.69 Japanese yen, down from 107.49; 1.4988 Swiss 
francs, up from 1.4947; 1.4709 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4692. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6549, up from $1.6517.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 106.72 yen and  
the pound was worth $1.6512. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8389 German marks, up from 1.8328; 
6.1673 French francs, up from 6.1471; 2.0719 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.0651; 1,820.49 Italian lire, up from 1,814.52. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed Monday in London at $318.60 bid per troy ounce, down  
from $323.00 on Friday. In Zurich the bid price was $318.00, down 
from $320.05. Gold fell $2.00 in Hong Kong to close at $318.50. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.59 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.62. 
  	   	
