<HEADLINE> Bird Pleased With Pacers' Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Larry Bird has completed what he says is his  
final training camp as coach of the Indiana Pacers, praising the 
work of his players on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Guys really worked hard until the last day. The last practice  
that we held, I think everybody wanted to get home,'' Bird said 
after sending the team through a morning practice at Market Square 
Arena, where the team was holding a free public scrimmage and 
autograph session in the evening. 
</P>
<P>
