<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Warrick Dunn Sprains Left Knee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Tampa Bay Buccaneers running back Warrick  
Dunn sprained his left knee late in the Bucs' 26-23 loss to the 
Green Bay Packers on Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Dunn, who had 1,026 yards rushing last season, was hurt during  
Tampa Bay's final scoring drive of the game. He caught a short pass 
from Trent Dilfer at the Tampa Bay 39 near the Buccaneers' sideline 
and was tackled awkwardly by Green Bay linebacker Brian Williams. 
</P>
<P>
	Dunn lay on the field for several minutes but eventually hopped  
off under his own power. He didn't return to the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Team doctors said afterward that he had sprained the knee. The  
Buccaneers are off next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Before the injury, Dunn had an excellent game with six pass  
receptions for 41 yards and 14 rushes for 39 yards. With 22 
catches, Dunn is second in the league behind Green Bay's Dorsey 
Levens for receptions by a running back. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
