<HEADLINE> Mets Put Tickets for Braves on Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tickets for the New York Mets' home games  
against Atlanta in the National League Championship Series next 
weekend will go on sale Tuesday at Shea Stadium and by telephone, 
team officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	For fans at the ballpark, numbered wristbands will be  
distributed at 7 a.m. Tuesday. The Mets will randomly select the 
starting number and announce it at 9:15 a.m. Only cash will be 
accepted at the ballpark. 
</P>
<P>
	Telephone sales start at 10 a.m., and only American Express,  
Discover, MasterCard and Visa will be accepted. There is a service 
charge of $6 per ticket for phone orders. 
</P>
<P>
	Most tickets are priced between $50 and $70. Each fan may  
purchase up to eight tickets per game. 
</P>
<P>
	New York is home for Games 3-5 of the seven-game series, with  
Game 3 scheduled for Friday night at 8:12. Saturday's game is 
scheduled for 7:42 p.m., and Sunday's, if necessary, will begin at 
4:09 p.m. 




  	   	
