<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Monday, Oct. 11, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	New Nasdaq High; Dow Ends Off 1.58  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Nasdaq composite index pushed to a record  
high close today as the promise of strong corporate earnings pumped 
up technology stocks. It rose 29.48 to 2,916.05, surpassing its 
all-time closing high of 2,887.06, set Sept. 10. The Dow Jones 
industrial average, meanwhile, closed down 1.58 at 10,648.18, 
having given up an earlier gain of as much as 69 points. Other 
broader measures were little changed in quiet trading. Traders said 
the modest performance was somewhat expected after last week, when 
the Dow gained almost 377 points in its best performance in three 
months. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10,648.18  -  1.58
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1,366  Declines 1,573  Unchgd  553
NYSE Volume:         616,155,500
