<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Abercrombie &AMP; Fitch Co., up 1/2 at 34 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	A Merrill Lynch analyst said rumors that the company's business  
has slowed are unfounded. Shares of Abercrombie, a casual clothing 
retailer popular with high school and college students, fell 
steeply Friday amid speculation sales were down. 

</P>
<P>
 *E.W. Scripps Co., down 1 1/2 at 49 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The publishing company said it earned 36 cents a share in the  
third quarter. Wall Street analysts anticipated earnings of 40 
cents a share. Scripps cited weak advertising in its TV station 
group. 

</P>
<P>
 *Abbott Laboratories, up 5/8 at 41 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Abbott earned 38 cents per share in the third quarter, in line  
with analysts' estimates. Profits rose more than 10 percent from 
last year's third quarter, and sales rose despite the company's 
struggle to remarket its anti-clotting drug Abbokinase. 

</P>
<P>
 *Authentic Fitness Corp., up 2 1/4 at 19 13/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Warnaco Group Inc. offered to buy Authentic Fitness for  
$20.50 a share in cash, or about $412 million. Warnaco, an apparel 
maker, made an unsuccessful bid for Authentic Fitness, the maker of 
Speedo swimwear, in 1996. 

</P>
<P>
 *Stryker Corp., up 4 15/16 at 58 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	A Deutsche Banc Alex. Brown analyst raised his rating on the  
stock, saying Stryker should post strong earnings growth over the 
next three years. Stryker makes speciality surgical products. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Knight/Trimark Group Inc., down 3 39/64 at 26 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Jersey City, N.J., securities dealer expects to post  
third-quarter earnings of 17 to 19 cents a share, well below 
analysts' expectations of 30 cents a share. Knight/Trimark cited 
stock market volatility and lower trading volume. 

</P>
<P>
 *Ask Jeeves Inc., up 17 7/8 at 68 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Microsoft has agreed to use Ask Jeeves's service to answer  
questions regarding its Windows 98 operating System. Ask Jeeves 
makes technology that provides automated answers to 
natural-language computer questions. 

</P>
<P>
 *Vantive Corp., up 3 at 11 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	PeopleSoft, a maker of business management software, plans to  
acquire Vantive for $433 million, or $14.23 per share. Vantive 
makes customer service software. The combined company will focus on 
electronic commerce. 

</P>
<P>
 *Puma Technology Inc., up 13 1/2 at 35 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Puma said Monday it will launch Intellisync.com, a free Internet  
synchronization service, in the first quarter of 2000. Puma said 
the service lets users align personal computer applications, mobile 
devices, and Web-based content at one Internet address. 




  	   	
</P>
