<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AskJeeves Soars After Microsoft Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
                       *Dow Jones News Service    	
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (Dow Jones News) -- Shares of AskJeeves Inc. soared by  
more than 35 percent Monday after Microsoft Corp. said it would use 
an AskJeeves service to provide online technical support for the 
Windows 98 operating system. 
</P>
<P>
	AskJeeves, Emeryville, Calif., operates a popular Web site  
searches the Internet to find answers to questions users type in 
ordinary English. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of AskJeeves rose $17.87 1/2 to close at $68.31 1/4 on the  
Nasdaq Stock Market. About 4 million shares changed hands, more 
than 11 times their average daily volume. 
</P>
<P>
	Neither company disclosed financial specifics, but AskJeeves  
Chief Executive Rob Wrubel said the agreement would generate more 
than seven figures during the next 12 months. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of Microsoft, based in Redmond, Wash., fell 62 1/2 cents to  
$94.31 1/4, also on Nasdaq. 


</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
